The paper discusses the analysis of reviews, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques, suggesting that it could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the challenges of working with noisy and incomplete text, which could fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The development of an interactive system for review analysis suggests that the paper could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories.
